Synopsis:
   $rest(<start> <text>)

Technical:
   The $rest() function returns the given test starting at the position
   specified by <start>.

Practical:
   This function is mostly useful when you know you want to always remove
   the first few characters from an input string, regardless of what they
   are.
   
Returns:
   <text> with <start> number of characters removed from the front

Examples:
   $rest(4 foobarfnord)                 returns "arfnord"

See Also:
   left(6); right(6); mid(6)

